# PPE Detection with YOLO11n

A real-time object detection web app that identifies **Personal Protective Equipment (PPE)** in images using a custom-trained YOLO11n model. Upload an image and the app draws bounding boxes around detected items and reports how many of each class it found.

Built with [Ultralytics YOLO11](https://docs.ultralytics.com/) for detection and [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/) for the web interface.

---

## Features

- Upload any image (JPG / JPEG / PNG) and run detection in the browser
- Side-by-side view of the original and annotated image — no scrolling to see results
- Adjustable **confidence threshold** slider to filter weak detections
- Per-class detection summary with object counts
- Lightweight `yolo11n` model for fast inference on CPU

---

## Model

- **Architecture:** YOLO11n (the *nano* variant — smallest and fastest in the YOLO11 family)
- **Framework:** Ultralytics
- **Weights:** `best.pt` (produced from training on the dataset below)

YOLO11n was chosen for its small size and quick inference, which makes it well suited to free-tier deployment where CPU and memory are limited.

---

## Dataset

Trained on the **PPE** dataset from Roboflow Universe:

**https://universe.roboflow.com/ppe1-qla6c/ppe-gzzdx**

The dataset contains annotated images of workers wearing protective equipment. Export it from Roboflow in **YOLO11 / YOLOv8 format**, which gives you the `data.yaml` file and the `train` / `valid` / `test` splits needed for training.

The model is trained to detect **4 classes**:

| # | Class  |
|---|--------|
| 0 | helmet |
| 1 | vest   |
| 2 | glove  |
| 3 | pants  |

