## Installation

Clone the repository and install the dependencies:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/jahanzeb-Ali/ppe-Personal-Protective-Equipment-.git
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**requirements.txt**

```
streamlit
ultralytics
opencv-python-headless
```

> `opencv-python-headless` is used instead of the regular `opencv-python` because deployment servers have no display libraries, which otherwise causes a `libGL.so.1` error.

---

## Running Locally

```bash
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

Then open the URL shown in the terminal (usually `http://localhost:8501`). Upload an image from the sidebar to run detection.

---

## Training

The model was trained with the Ultralytics CLI. After exporting the dataset from Roboflow, run:

```bash
yolo detect train \
    model=yolo11n.pt \
    data=path/to/data.yaml \
    epochs=100 \
    imgsz=640
```

The best-performing weights are saved to `runs/detect/train/weights/best.pt`. Copy that file into the project root as `best.pt`.

> Adjust `epochs`, `imgsz`, and other hyperparameters to match what you actually used.

